    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "ABOUT FLIPACLIP\n\nFlipaClip https://flipaclip.com/es/ is the world’s biggest animation app with over +90 million lifetime installs.\n\nFlipaClip turns any mobile device into an animation studio.\n\nAnimated movies and shows require massive budgets, years of production, or the approval of a handful of studios to exist. That’s how the industry has worked for decades.\n\nVery soon, a blockbuster animated movie will be entirely produced by a 15-year old in her parent’s basement. On a phone. And it will be made and distributed for $0.\n\nWe are on it.\n\n\nKEY RESPONSIBILITIES\n\n - Own the delivery and long-term operation of high-impact backend systems, from architecture to production.\n\n - Set and evolve backend processes, engineering standards, and technical best practices.\n\n - Define and actively use KPIs covering system reliability, development speed, data quality, and error rates.\n\n - Make system-level architectural decisions and technical tradeoffs with a clear understanding of impact.\n\n - Establish automated testing and validation processes that reduce regressions and operational risk.\n\n - Introduce AI-assisted development workflows where they increase leverage, with strong validation and safety mechanisms.\n\n - Communicate progress, risks, and technical decisions clearly across engineering and product stakeholders.\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n - 5+ years building and maintaining with AWS\n\n - Demonstrable experience delivering high-impact backend systems and projects that operate successfully in production\n\n - Strong experience building backend services for mobile applications (iOS/Android)\n\n - Ownership: Strong sense of ownership, strategic thinking, and a solution-first mindset\n\n - Management: Creating structure where needed. Processes, standards, and objectives that teams actually follow.\n\n - Product-minded: Able to balance engineering quality with pragmatic trade-offs to move fast.\n\n - Customer-obsessed: Making technical decisions with a clear understanding of how they affect customers, product quality, and our overall business.\n\n - Solid experience working with Node.js and TypeScript\n\n - Strong understanding of modern React frameworks\n\n - Experience with Docker and containerized deployments\n\n - Solid understanding of RESTful API design and implementation\n\n - Interest in or experience with Generative AI and related technologies\n\n\nNICE TO HAVE\n\n - Hands-on experience working on AI/ML or LLM-based products.\n\n - Experience with NestJS framework\n\n - Python experience, particularly with Apache Airflow or similar ETL tools\n\n - Knowledge of Firebase (Authentication, Firestore, Remote Config)\n\n - Experience with Infrastructure-as-Code (Pulumi or Terraform)\n\n - Familiarity with observability tools (OpenTelemetry, Signoz, or similar)\n\n - Experience with video streaming technologies (HLS, MediaConvert)\n\n - Knowledge of analytics platforms (Amplitude, MoEngage, or similar)\n\n - Experience with ElasticSearch or similar search technologies\n\n - Understanding of mobile app backend requirements (iOS/Android)\n\n - Experience with subscription/payment integrations (Purchasely, RevenueCat, IAP)\n\n\nOUR TECH STACK\n\nBackend\n\n - Node.js (14/16) with NestJS and Restify frameworks\n\n - Python 3.9 for ETL and data pipelines\n\n - Apache Airflow 2.7.3 for workflow orchestration\n\n - JWT-based authentication\n\n - Sequelize ORM\n\nFrontend\n\n - Next.js 15 with App Router\n\n - React 18/19 with TypeScript\n\n - Tailwind CSS for styling\n\n - Zustand for state management\n\n - SWR for data fetching\n\n - Radix UI component library\n\n - Infrastructure \u0026 DevOps\n\n - AWS (ECS Fargate, S3, RDS, ElastiCache, SQS, CloudFront, MediaConvert)\n\n - Docker and Docker Compose\n\n - Pulumi for Infrastructure-as-Code\n\n - GitHub Actions for CI/CD\n\n - Vercel for frontend deployments\n\nData \u0026 Storage\n\n - MySQL and PostgreSQL (AWS RDS)\n\n - Redis (AWS ElastiCache)\n\n - ElasticSearch for search functionality\n\n - Firebase Firestore\n\n - AWS S3 and Cloudflare R2 for asset storage\n\nObservability\n\n - Signoz with OpenTelemetry (OTLP)\n\n - Winston for structured logging\n\n - Slack webhooks for alerting\n\n\nTHE SELECTION PROCESS\n\n - Silver.dev Recruiter Screen\n\n - Silver.dev Live Coding Screen\n\n - Behavioral Screen with FlipaClip's CAO\n\n - Work Experience Overview + some Technical Discussion with FlipaClip's COO\n\n - Final Screen with FlipaClip's CEO",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
